WEBVTT

00:16.150 --> 00:19.718
- [groans] It's overheated.
It won't start.

00:19.720 --> 00:21.420
- We're not even close
to safety.

00:21.422 --> 00:23.655
- No, we're miles
and miles away.

00:23.657 --> 00:25.657
- What do we do?

00:25.659 --> 00:27.226
- I don't think
we have a choice.

00:27.228 --> 00:29.395
I mean, it won't start
until it cools down.

00:29.397 --> 00:34.033
- We can carry on in my truck.
There's enough room.

00:34.035 --> 00:35.384
- Mm.
- That's a good idea.

00:35.385 --> 00:36.734
- I'll catch up with you
once I get it running.

00:36.737 --> 00:39.271
- But we're not going
without you.

00:39.273 --> 00:40.990
- I can't leave this.
I can't leave my research.

00:40.991 --> 00:42.708
I think it's the best chance
we have to get through all this.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.343
- Yeah.
- Take the kids.

00:44.345 --> 00:47.379
- We're not going
without you.

00:47.381 --> 00:49.214
- You and Martin go.

00:49.216 --> 00:50.816
- The mission's still on.
We'll wait.

00:50.818 --> 00:52.251
- She's right.
The mission is on.

00:52.253 --> 00:54.186
You're stuck.

00:54.188 --> 00:55.788
- I'm gonna go, uh,
look around.

00:59.427 --> 01:00.659
- Hey.

01:02.797 --> 01:05.431
How are you doing?

01:05.433 --> 01:07.166
- Great, Dana.

01:07.168 --> 01:09.101
You know, I just killed somebody
I loved, but thanks for asking.

01:09.103 --> 01:10.269
I'm awesome.

01:10.271 --> 01:12.071
- You didn't kill him, Bree.

01:12.073 --> 01:13.405
- I could have saved him.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.641
- How?

01:15.643 --> 01:18.410
- Loving him more.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.512
- Bree, don't you think
that's...

01:20.514 --> 01:23.449
a little bit unrealistic?

01:23.451 --> 01:25.451
- Really, Dana?

01:25.453 --> 01:27.519
Unrealistic?
You want to go there?

01:27.521 --> 01:30.155
How old's your boyfriend?
What, like, 32?

01:30.157 --> 01:32.558
- [stammers]
- 28.

01:32.560 --> 01:34.359
- You know, I always thought
that when you got started,

01:34.361 --> 01:37.329
it would be, like, some math guy
or something, not some fling.

01:37.331 --> 01:40.099
- He's not a fling.

01:40.101 --> 01:42.167
Bree, look,
I know you're hurting.

01:42.169 --> 01:43.368
- [scoffs]

01:43.370 --> 01:45.204
- But none of us are
to blame for this.

01:45.206 --> 01:47.106
- Yes, we are!

01:47.108 --> 01:49.475
It is my fault, Dana.

01:49.477 --> 01:52.811
I'm the only one to blame.

01:52.813 --> 01:54.780
Devyn's dead,
and it's on me.

01:59.520 --> 02:01.453
- Poor girl.
She cried all night.

02:01.455 --> 02:04.123
I'm worried about her.

02:04.125 --> 02:06.458
- I'm worried about you.
- Why me?

02:06.460 --> 02:07.526
- What do you mean why you?

02:07.528 --> 02:08.861
Yesterday you killed
four people.

02:08.863 --> 02:10.796
- You killed four people
in Seattle.

02:10.798 --> 02:12.364
- You knew that?
- Of course.

02:12.366 --> 02:16.235
Dana told me that night.
- Why didn't you mention it?

02:16.237 --> 02:18.504
- Look, it was a good plan.
I'm proud of you.

02:18.506 --> 02:19.571
What's the plan for this?

02:19.573 --> 02:21.406
The volcano could blow
any second.

02:21.408 --> 02:24.376
- We're gonna get ten miles down
the road and break down again.

02:24.378 --> 02:26.512
We just...we've got time.

02:26.514 --> 02:28.480
- Okay.
- We could talk.

02:28.482 --> 02:30.849
- [scoffs]
Talk.

02:30.851 --> 02:34.453
Uh, yeah, no, I want to.
I want to.

02:34.455 --> 02:36.421
Right after
we're out of this.

02:41.695 --> 02:43.495
- Jeez, Mom,
don't you ever knock?

02:43.497 --> 02:46.198
- Wow.
[laughs] Wow.

02:46.200 --> 02:48.734
I've never needed to knock.
It's my RV, is it not?

02:48.736 --> 02:51.803
Step forward, sir.
- Welcome to my mother's stare.

02:51.805 --> 02:53.839
I've been getting it
for years.

02:53.841 --> 02:55.674
- I'm okay with it.

02:55.676 --> 02:57.643
- We'll see. What's your name?
- Martin James Winters.

02:57.645 --> 02:59.211
- How do you know Booner?

02:59.213 --> 03:00.879
- A Ranger buddy hooked me up
six months ago.

03:00.881 --> 03:03.282
- You know a ranger?
- Did six years, ma'am.

03:03.284 --> 03:05.217
- What's your battalion?
- That's classified.

03:05.219 --> 03:06.952
- That's right.
Deployment?

03:06.954 --> 03:08.554
- Iraq and Afghanistan.
- Any tin?

03:08.556 --> 03:10.422
- Campaign medals, bronze star,
purple heart.

03:10.424 --> 03:12.791
- Purple heart. Where?
- Right leg, ma'am--

03:12.793 --> 03:14.560
through and through.
- Upper, lower?

03:14.562 --> 03:16.728
- Upper.
- Has she seen the scar?

03:16.730 --> 03:18.964
- Mom, yeah, I've--
I've seen the scar.

03:22.870 --> 03:24.803
- Little girls like scars 'cause
they don't know any better.

03:24.805 --> 03:26.638
- Mom, I'm not
a little girl anymore.

03:26.640 --> 03:27.956
- Are you playing
with my daughter?

03:27.957 --> 03:29.273
- No, ma'am.
- Did you volunteer for this

03:29.276 --> 03:30.409
because of my daughter?
- Yes, ma'am.

03:30.411 --> 03:32.544
- Why?

03:32.546 --> 03:33.946
- Don't answer that.
- Answer that.

03:33.948 --> 03:35.714
- Because
she's beautiful, ma'am...

03:35.716 --> 03:38.717
and very smart, and I can't stop
thinking about her.

03:38.719 --> 03:41.987
- Yes, she is smart.
What do you like about this guy?

03:41.989 --> 03:45.757
- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
what he said.

03:47.895 --> 03:48.994
- Plus, I'm funny.

03:48.996 --> 03:51.563
- I'm funnier.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.232
- She's definitely funnier.

03:58.405 --> 04:02.307
There are a thousand ways
to die--you both know that.

04:02.309 --> 04:04.710
If Dad doesn't get this thing
going and the volcano blows,

04:04.712 --> 04:05.844
we could all die right here.

04:05.846 --> 04:08.513
In light of that...

04:08.515 --> 04:10.515
be good to each other.

04:10.517 --> 04:11.750
- Yep.
- Yes, ma'am.

04:11.752 --> 04:13.919
- Please.

04:22.630 --> 04:25.297
Great.

04:25.299 --> 04:26.665
- Yeah.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.400
But looking at your face,
I'm gonna guess

04:28.402 --> 04:31.637
that, uh, you were
just talking to Dana?

04:31.639 --> 04:33.005
- You knew about him?

04:33.007 --> 04:34.306
- Yeah, since the Alamo.

04:34.308 --> 04:36.908
- And you didn't tell me?

04:36.910 --> 04:38.644
- I thought it was
kind of obvious.

04:38.646 --> 04:41.613
- Uh-huh.
- He's a good guy.

04:41.615 --> 04:44.049
- A good guy. Yeah, okay,
he's a good guy, uh-huh.

04:44.051 --> 04:46.518
He'll be great for her.
Love it. Love it.

04:46.520 --> 04:48.620
- We have to pick up our talk.
- No, we don't.

04:48.622 --> 04:50.355
- It's not good enough...
- What?

04:50.357 --> 04:51.890
- For some of us
to live through this.

04:51.892 --> 04:55.427
Unless we all survive,
then everything is for nothing.

04:55.429 --> 04:57.829
- Well, the number-one rule
of survival is don't die,

04:57.831 --> 04:59.031
make the other person die.

04:59.033 --> 05:00.499
- There are different kinds
of death.

05:00.501 --> 05:01.900
- Really?
Name two.

05:01.902 --> 05:04.002
- What if we make it through
all this, but the price of it

05:04.004 --> 05:06.071
is that we die spiritually?

05:06.073 --> 05:08.040
That's what we're risking
when we kill these people.

05:08.042 --> 05:10.375
- Josh, I get us through things.
That's what I do.

05:10.377 --> 05:13.512
That's my job.
I'm not mystical.

05:13.514 --> 05:17.349
That spiritual stuff,
I really don't understand.

05:17.351 --> 05:19.418
- We got to go!
We got to go!

05:19.420 --> 05:20.652
- It's okay.

05:20.654 --> 05:22.087
The engine is still cooling.
It's all right.

05:22.089 --> 05:23.922
- The mountain's blowing steam.
- No, it's fine.

05:23.924 --> 05:25.023
Until there's tremors,
we're all safe.

05:25.025 --> 05:26.024
- Honey...

05:26.026 --> 05:27.059
[rumbling]

05:27.061 --> 05:29.961
[all screaming]

05:38.005 --> 05:40.972
<i> [ominous music]</i>

05:40.974 --> 05:47.946
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:56.423 --> 05:58.990
<i> - I just don't want</i>
<i> to ride with Dana.</i>

05:58.992 --> 06:00.892
Like, I get that they should be
happy and everything.

06:00.894 --> 06:02.461
It's just, like...

06:02.463 --> 06:04.096
too much.

06:04.098 --> 06:06.465
- Yeah, I know.

06:11.605 --> 06:12.871
- Who is that?

06:15.976 --> 06:18.543
- That's my boy.

06:18.545 --> 06:22.514
- Ah, he's cute.
- Aww, that's sweet.

06:22.516 --> 06:25.384
- He passed away about a year
ago, before all this started.

06:25.386 --> 06:27.119
- Jane, I'm so sorry.
- We didn't know.

06:27.121 --> 06:28.954
I'm so sorry.

06:28.956 --> 06:30.756
- He was supposed to be
getting better,

06:30.758 --> 06:32.591
so I took a deployment.

06:32.593 --> 06:35.527
And then he didn't.

06:35.529 --> 06:39.398
And I never got a chance
to say good-bye.

06:39.400 --> 06:40.699
- Where's his dad?

06:40.701 --> 06:43.635
- Where's anyone anymore?

06:46.173 --> 06:48.807
- I'm sorry.
Jane, I'm sorry.

06:51.178 --> 06:52.611
- Look, I'm telling you this

06:52.613 --> 06:55.747
because you lost someone
yesterday,

06:55.749 --> 06:59.584
and if I were you,
I would deal with it.

06:59.586 --> 07:01.486
And I never did.

07:03.490 --> 07:05.090
- Since when do you care
about Moon Dog?

07:05.092 --> 07:07.526
- We'll live or die based
on which way the volcano erupts.

07:07.528 --> 07:09.127
And he might know.

07:09.129 --> 07:10.695
<i> - [over radio]</i>
<i> Paperweights these days,</i>

07:10.697 --> 07:12.464
<i> and I tell 'em straight,</i>

07:12.466 --> 07:14.599
<i> I tell 'em all</i>
<i> both less and great,</i>

07:14.601 --> 07:16.935
<i> it is the beast from the East</i>

07:16.937 --> 07:19.604
<i> where the boat of Ra pulls out</i>
<i> from every morning,</i>

07:19.606 --> 07:22.707
<i> oh, my chicks and Chicklets.</i>

07:22.709 --> 07:25.544
<i> 70 miles of death</i>
<i> in 3 directions,</i>

07:25.546 --> 07:27.112
<i> 10 to 20 to the west.</i>

07:27.114 --> 07:30.115
<i> So let's remember</i>
<i> that Greely lie.</i>

07:30.117 --> 07:32.083
<i> Go west, young man,</i>

07:32.085 --> 07:34.786
<i> 'cause you go East,</i>
<i> and you will die.</i>

07:34.788 --> 07:36.988
- Shit.
- What?

07:36.990 --> 07:39.558
- We're going east.
- Turn around. Go west.

07:39.560 --> 07:40.892
- We can't.
We can't do that.

07:40.894 --> 07:42.761
We'll just head back
into the volcano.

07:42.763 --> 07:45.030
- Okay, north or south.
- There's no other roads.

07:45.032 --> 07:47.098
<i> - [over radio] Remind us</i>
<i> that life is one sweet kiss</i>

07:47.100 --> 07:48.967
<i> and then turn off the bliss.</i>

07:48.969 --> 07:51.069
<i> This next load goes</i>

07:51.070 --> 07:53.170
<i> to all those chrome-dome</i>
<i> strangers on the road,</i>

07:53.173 --> 07:56.107
<i> looking for a place</i>
<i> to lay their hats tonight.</i>

07:56.109 --> 07:58.910
<i> Godspeed, all travelers.</i>

07:58.912 --> 08:00.512
- You're right.
There's no roads north or south.

08:00.514 --> 08:01.513
- Let me see.

08:03.484 --> 08:05.951
- Dad, look out!
- Aah!

08:07.721 --> 08:12.624
- What the hell?
- For God's sake.

08:12.626 --> 08:15.126
Oh, did you see that?

08:15.128 --> 08:16.661
Where'd he go?

08:16.663 --> 08:18.597
[knock at door]

08:22.102 --> 08:24.936
- Wait, Matt. Okay.

08:26.807 --> 08:27.939
- Okay.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.180
- Room for one more?

08:35.182 --> 08:36.882
- Why don't you back up first?

08:44.892 --> 08:46.291
- Who are you?

08:49.062 --> 08:50.795
- I've only just arrived.

08:50.797 --> 08:52.030
- What's your name?

08:54.535 --> 08:55.600
- Monk.

08:58.739 --> 09:00.772
- Where are your shoes?

09:03.844 --> 09:05.977
- Where they belong,
of course--

09:05.979 --> 09:07.846
away from my feet.

09:07.848 --> 09:09.881
- [groans]

09:09.883 --> 09:13.919
- Razor, Book of Mormon,
tea leaves.

09:15.088 --> 09:16.288
There's no weapon.

09:16.290 --> 09:18.023
- [clears throat]
- Well, I'm from Tibet.

09:18.025 --> 09:21.593
This body is my new vessel.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.130
My monastery vanished
in the blink of an eye.

09:25.132 --> 09:27.132
- When?

09:27.134 --> 09:30.168
- I don't know.

09:30.170 --> 09:32.571
I entered the void,
where there is no time.

09:32.573 --> 09:36.575
I woke up here...

09:36.577 --> 09:37.709
in this vessel.

09:37.711 --> 09:40.679
<i> [ominous music]</i>

09:40.681 --> 09:42.781
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:42.783 --> 09:44.316
- Sniper! Get down!

09:44.318 --> 09:45.850
[gunshots]

09:45.852 --> 09:47.819
Take cover behind the truck!

09:47.821 --> 09:51.990
[gunshots]

09:51.992 --> 09:54.893
Martin!

09:54.895 --> 09:57.829
[bullets whizzing]

10:01.802 --> 10:02.934
- Get in! Get in!

10:02.936 --> 10:04.903
- Take cover, honey!

10:04.905 --> 10:07.806
[gunshots]

10:07.808 --> 10:09.207
- Martin, do you have eyes?

10:09.209 --> 10:10.275
- Somewhere in those rocks!

10:10.277 --> 10:12.043
- Ugh.

10:12.045 --> 10:15.080
Is this you?
Huh, buddy?

10:15.082 --> 10:17.115
You setting us up?
- I'm by myself.

10:17.117 --> 10:19.751
- You better get cover.

10:19.753 --> 10:21.152
- I have nothing
to protect.

10:21.154 --> 10:23.822
- [groans]
- Dad's been hit!

10:23.824 --> 10:25.123
Dad!
- Stay here!

10:26.994 --> 10:28.727
- Honey!

10:28.729 --> 10:30.795
Honey!

10:30.797 --> 10:33.264
God, stay down. Stay down.
Stay down.

10:33.266 --> 10:34.966
- [groaning]

10:37.270 --> 10:39.237
- Put pressure.

10:39.239 --> 10:40.805
Put your head down.
Put your head down.

10:40.807 --> 10:42.841
- [groaning]

10:42.843 --> 10:45.644
- Get down!
He's gonna see you!

10:45.646 --> 10:48.179
- I'm the one who sees.

10:48.181 --> 10:55.153
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:58.091 --> 11:00.358
[explosion]

11:07.801 --> 11:13.705
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:13.707 --> 11:15.006
- Did you just kill that guy?

11:15.008 --> 11:16.741
- Dad!

11:18.945 --> 11:20.278
Get him up.
Get him up.

11:20.280 --> 11:21.846
- Be careful.
- Careful, careful.

11:21.848 --> 11:25.417
- Be gentle. Be gentle.
- Okay, come on.

11:25.419 --> 11:27.852
- Okay, okay.
- Careful.

11:31.758 --> 11:34.025
- The freaking truck is dead--
shot through the radiator.

11:34.027 --> 11:36.961
- [groaning]

11:40.333 --> 11:42.834
- We have many things
to discuss.

11:44.838 --> 11:48.173
- Dad is not gonna die,
so stop it.

11:48.175 --> 11:49.774
Stop thinking about it.

11:49.776 --> 11:52.744
- Thinking about what?

11:52.746 --> 11:54.746
- Dana...

11:54.748 --> 11:57.482
he's not gonna die,
all right?

11:57.484 --> 11:59.317
- That's not
what I was thinking about.

11:59.319 --> 12:01.886
- You know why Mom made you ride
with me, right?

12:01.888 --> 12:03.354
So that I'd stop thinking
about Devyn.

12:03.356 --> 12:05.023
And you being like this
is not helping me.

12:05.025 --> 12:07.158
- Well, because I'm scared.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.460
What if he dies?

12:08.462 --> 12:11.229
- He's not gonna die, okay?
He's...

12:11.231 --> 12:13.798
'Cause he...
It's not gonna happen.

12:13.800 --> 12:15.900
- Well, that is some
poor reasoning.

12:15.902 --> 12:18.203
- Yeah, well,
logic isn't everything, okay?

12:18.205 --> 12:20.839
Your twin voodoo or whatever
told you that I wasn't dead.

12:20.841 --> 12:23.942
I know Dad is not gonna die.
It's the same thing.

12:23.944 --> 12:26.778
Think of something else.

12:26.780 --> 12:28.046
- I can't.

12:28.048 --> 12:30.048
- Dana, I swear.

12:30.050 --> 12:31.416
He is not gonna die.

12:31.418 --> 12:33.351
- Is that
your new mantra now?

12:33.353 --> 12:35.420
- I don't know
what a mantra is.

12:35.422 --> 12:38.189
- It's just a phrase that--
- I don't care what a mantra is.

12:38.191 --> 12:41.893
Would you drive
with me, please?

12:41.895 --> 12:43.895
- [groaning]
It burns.

12:43.897 --> 12:45.997
- Honey, we're gonna have to
take the round out, all right?

12:45.999 --> 12:48.133
- How bad is it?
How bad is it?

12:48.135 --> 12:51.269
- It's enough that we're gonna
take the round out.

12:51.271 --> 12:52.904
Guys...

12:52.906 --> 12:55.507
- Anesthesia?
- It's local.

12:55.509 --> 12:58.076
- Let me do it.
- What are you doing?

12:58.078 --> 13:00.245
- Let him try.
- Let me take care of it.

13:00.247 --> 13:04.149
- Karen, Karen, let him try.

13:04.151 --> 13:06.151
[groaning]

13:06.153 --> 13:07.452
- Okay.

13:07.454 --> 13:10.388
<i> [dramatic mystical music]</i>

13:10.390 --> 13:17.328
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:20.233 --> 13:23.234
- Baby, I'm here
with you, okay?

13:23.236 --> 13:26.337
- [groaning]
- The bullet missed your organs.

13:26.339 --> 13:29.440
Very lucky. Very lucky.

13:29.442 --> 13:31.409
- Okay.

13:31.411 --> 13:34.145
Ohh!
- Aah!

13:34.147 --> 13:35.880
- Ooh.

13:35.882 --> 13:38.216
What are you doing?

13:38.218 --> 13:40.251
Stay with me, Josh.

13:40.253 --> 13:41.853
- What the hell?

13:41.855 --> 13:44.322
- [grunting]

13:44.324 --> 13:47.559
- Are you with me?
- Yeah.

13:47.561 --> 13:49.994
- Dad, Dad, Dad, Dad.

13:49.996 --> 13:51.496
- Come on.

13:51.498 --> 13:53.264
It's all right.
- Oh, shit.

13:53.266 --> 13:56.434
- It's all right.

13:56.436 --> 13:59.070
- It's fine.
It's okay. It's okay.

13:59.072 --> 14:00.572
- [breathing heavily]

14:00.574 --> 14:02.540
- And here's your bullet.

14:05.512 --> 14:07.912
Will you take it, please?
Do you have a towel?

14:07.914 --> 14:09.414
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Here's one.

14:09.416 --> 14:11.216
- We have Chitosan
to stop the bleeding.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.985
- No, no, it's not necessary.
Can you get my bag, please?

14:13.987 --> 14:16.387
I'm gonna
bandage him up, okay?

14:16.389 --> 14:18.590
- Shh.
- He'll be fine.

14:18.592 --> 14:21.926
This is better
than stitches.

14:21.928 --> 14:23.561
- What happened?
- No, no, he's just--

14:23.563 --> 14:26.497
He's sleeping.
We're gonna let him rest.

14:26.499 --> 14:31.936
Tea leaves. Slightly, here so he
heals up really well.

14:31.938 --> 14:34.072
See the color
coming back to his face?

14:34.074 --> 14:38.076
Let's let him rest.
Let's just let him rest.

14:39.613 --> 14:41.212
I hope you don't mind
my saying this...

14:41.214 --> 14:43.181
- I'm sure I will.

14:43.183 --> 14:45.049
- I see that you care deeply
for your family.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.385
- Obviously I do.
- But you're troubled

14:47.387 --> 14:49.220
by the number of people
that you've killed.

14:49.222 --> 14:51.222
- I don't know.
You just killed somebody.

14:51.224 --> 14:53.157
- Killing involves death.
Death is an illusion.

14:53.159 --> 14:55.593
Therefore...
- Therefore, bullshit.

14:55.595 --> 14:58.029
Killing is real.

14:58.031 --> 15:00.531
- Huh, what is real?
Am I real?

15:00.533 --> 15:03.101
- Apparently.
- But you wish that I wasn't.

15:03.103 --> 15:05.503
- That's not what I wish.
I don't know what I wish.

15:05.505 --> 15:08.539
I know that I regret the people
that I've killed.

15:12.245 --> 15:13.912
- I can see that.
It's no mystery.

15:13.914 --> 15:15.480
- Okay.
- All right?

15:15.482 --> 15:17.348
To look at you is to know,

15:17.350 --> 15:19.284
it is to understand,
it is to feel.

15:22.022 --> 15:23.521
It'll be okay.

15:23.523 --> 15:27.558
- Hey, uh...
Martin's looking for you.

15:27.560 --> 15:29.127
- Okay.

15:39.072 --> 15:41.406
- Wow.
You're driving.

15:41.408 --> 15:43.374
- Yeah, Mom made me.

15:43.376 --> 15:46.311
How's Dad?
- He's asleep.

15:46.313 --> 15:47.679
He'll be okay.

15:49.616 --> 15:51.115
You drive pretty well.

15:51.117 --> 15:54.419
- Yeah, I know.
I used to steal a lot of cars.

15:58.258 --> 16:01.492
Matt, I'm scared.

16:01.494 --> 16:03.695
- Good.
You should be.

16:05.966 --> 16:07.298
You never stole cars.

16:07.300 --> 16:08.499
- I was with people
who stole cars.

16:08.501 --> 16:09.634
It was influential.

16:16.743 --> 16:18.676
- What if he dies?

16:18.678 --> 16:20.545
- He won't die.

16:20.547 --> 16:22.680
- People die
all the time now.

16:22.682 --> 16:25.049
- It's the end
of the world.

16:25.051 --> 16:27.185
- Well, yeah, but if
you extrapolate that...

16:27.187 --> 16:30.488
It's just statistically--
- Smaller word, please.

16:30.490 --> 16:33.591
- Okay, if you take
the situation

16:33.593 --> 16:36.160
and you project it
into the future--

16:36.162 --> 16:39.697
- Oh.
You mean "extrapolate."

16:39.699 --> 16:41.232
You could have
just said that.

16:41.234 --> 16:43.234
- [chuckles]
Yes.

16:43.236 --> 16:46.337
If you extrapolate
the death rate around here,

16:46.339 --> 16:49.507
then we all die.

16:52.045 --> 16:54.278
- I was in firefights
in Afghanistan.

16:54.280 --> 16:56.647
You know who dies?

16:56.649 --> 17:00.151
People who think
they're gonna die.

17:00.153 --> 17:02.020
I swear to God.

17:02.022 --> 17:04.589
Anyone who thought they were
coming back...

17:04.591 --> 17:06.190
came back.

17:10.563 --> 17:12.630
You think you're gonna die
anytime soon?

17:12.632 --> 17:16.234
- Honestly?

17:16.236 --> 17:17.335
No.

17:17.337 --> 17:18.636
I don't.

17:18.638 --> 17:20.671
- Yeah.
I don't either.

17:22.709 --> 17:25.209
Whatever this thing is...

17:25.211 --> 17:29.280
you and me, we're gonna be there
when it ends.

17:29.282 --> 17:32.817
We're gonna know each other
for the rest of our lives.

17:32.819 --> 17:35.787
- Okay...

17:35.789 --> 17:40.191
either I'm getting the flu,
or you're giving me chills.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.493
- It could be the flu.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.802
- It's not the flu.

17:58.278 --> 18:01.179
- [groaning]

18:04.584 --> 18:06.551
How long was I out?

18:06.552 --> 18:08.519
- A very brief time.
You must be strong.

18:08.521 --> 18:11.722
- Where are we?
- Still in danger.

18:11.724 --> 18:14.092
- Oh, what's new?
We're always in danger.

18:14.094 --> 18:15.460
- Well, this danger
is imminent.

18:15.462 --> 18:19.397
The volcano will erupt
and none of us will survive.

18:19.399 --> 18:21.833
- [sighs]
- What should we do?

18:21.835 --> 18:24.502
- Mm, I've passed
through life many times.

18:24.504 --> 18:27.872
I find the best preparation
is to sing your death song.

18:27.874 --> 18:29.574
- Yeah, I don't think
we're gonna be doing that.

18:29.576 --> 18:31.809
- Something else, then,
but we are out of time,

18:31.811 --> 18:35.179
and most certainly,
we're all going to die, so...

18:35.181 --> 18:37.315
- How do you know
we're gonna die?

18:37.317 --> 18:38.616
- Would you believe me
if I told you?

18:38.618 --> 18:40.184
- No.
- Hmm.

18:40.186 --> 18:44.188
- But you have an idea?
- I do, yes.

18:44.190 --> 18:45.590
Go back to the volcano.

18:45.592 --> 18:47.291
- [scoffs]
- Back to the volcano.

18:47.293 --> 18:49.794
- That's an awesome idea.
Why didn't I think of that?

18:49.796 --> 18:51.529
- There's
a prayer wheel on it,

18:51.531 --> 18:55.399
and I believe that that's why
this vessel brought me here.

18:55.401 --> 18:56.734
- What's a prayer wheel do?

18:56.736 --> 18:59.137
- It's something that grants
its possessor

18:59.139 --> 19:01.606
anything they desire most.
- Of course.

19:01.608 --> 19:03.374
- So you could stop
the volcano?

19:03.376 --> 19:05.877
- Mm! Mm...

19:05.879 --> 19:06.878
presumably.

19:06.880 --> 19:08.546
- Oh, right.

19:08.548 --> 19:11.415
So you just want us
to walk up an erupting volcano.

19:11.417 --> 19:13.918
- Do you really believe this?
- I'm in the business of belief.

19:13.920 --> 19:16.354
- Oh, so, if you could, say,
do that,

19:16.356 --> 19:18.356
um, why don't you just do it
yourself?

19:18.358 --> 19:20.391
- Because I'm not the one
who needs to be saved.

19:22.829 --> 19:26.631
I can surf the wave,
vessel to vessel, but...

19:26.633 --> 19:27.765
you can't.

19:29.335 --> 19:31.169
- D-do we need to talk
about this more?

19:31.171 --> 19:34.238
I mean, you're clearly...
completely insane.

19:34.240 --> 19:36.641
I'm gonna--
Honey, can we just, like, drive

19:36.643 --> 19:38.409
as fast as we can
and outrun this thing?

19:38.411 --> 19:40.678
- Oh, I regret to inform you,
that will be impossible.

19:43.249 --> 19:45.183
The road is destroyed.

19:45.185 --> 19:46.651
- Of course it is.
- Just ahead of us.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.486
- Uh-huh.

19:48.488 --> 19:51.789
- Mom!
Mom, come here a sec.

19:51.791 --> 19:52.790
Now!

19:54.360 --> 19:56.260
- What is it?

20:06.306 --> 20:08.439
- We're out of road.

20:13.313 --> 20:16.447
- What do we do?

20:16.449 --> 20:18.282
- Um, I'm gonna talk
to your dad.

20:18.284 --> 20:21.686
Uh, can I--can I be alone
with my husband?

20:21.688 --> 20:23.621
Thanks.
- Oh.

20:23.623 --> 20:25.456
- I think
we should go outside.

20:25.458 --> 20:27.725
- Honey, you've just been shot.
- No, no, no. I'm--I'm better.

20:27.727 --> 20:28.826
- Oh, okay.

20:28.828 --> 20:30.761
- Let's go.

20:30.763 --> 20:33.531
- Hey.
- Oh.

20:38.738 --> 20:41.672
[wind whooshing]

20:46.779 --> 20:47.979
- Do you believe
in miracles?

20:47.981 --> 20:49.880
- No.

20:49.882 --> 20:53.017
- I do. Karen, look...
- Yeah?

20:57.357 --> 20:59.690
- Holy shit.
- Yeah.

20:59.692 --> 21:01.025
Holy something.

21:01.027 --> 21:04.929
- [chuckles]

21:04.931 --> 21:06.831
I don't know. I don't know.
What do you want to do?

21:06.833 --> 21:09.867
<i>Believe in the guy?</i>
<i>Okay, let's go back.</i>

21:09.869 --> 21:11.802
<i> See the volcano.</i>
<i> - When Mount Rainer blows,</i>

21:11.804 --> 21:13.371
there's gonna be
a pyroclastic flow

21:13.373 --> 21:15.039
that's 2,000 degrees and moving
500 miles an hour.

21:15.041 --> 21:16.741
- Okay.

21:16.743 --> 21:19.277
There are avalanche shelters.
You're gonna go in 'em.

21:19.279 --> 21:21.679
- What are you gonna do?

21:21.681 --> 21:24.582
- [sighs] I'm gonna go find
the prayer wheel.

21:24.584 --> 21:27.051
- No, I'm--I'm gonna go find
the prayer wheel.

21:27.053 --> 21:29.687
- Oh, you're gonna go find it?
You just got shot.

21:29.689 --> 21:32.523
- I'm healed now.
- No, Josh.

21:35.061 --> 21:38.596
- You don't even believe in it.
- You do, and that's enough.

21:41.734 --> 21:43.668
I better get back.

21:58.951 --> 22:00.384
Mm-hmm.

22:00.386 --> 22:02.620
[explosion]

22:08.027 --> 22:09.960
All right.

22:09.962 --> 22:11.595
- Do you know how fast
an eruption travels?

22:11.597 --> 22:13.431
- Um, 500 miles an hour?

22:13.433 --> 22:15.366
- Yeah, it's like liquid cement
that's on fire.

22:15.368 --> 22:16.901
It's gonna burn you alive.

22:16.903 --> 22:18.836
- That's why
you're giving me this, right?

22:18.838 --> 22:20.871
[device beeps]
Track me.

22:20.873 --> 22:22.440
- How far up is this thing?

22:22.442 --> 22:23.974
- If there is even a thing.

22:23.976 --> 22:26.544
- Uh, well, how do I know?

22:26.546 --> 22:28.579
- The journey will not be long.
- There you go.

22:28.581 --> 22:30.715
- The prayer wheel should be
somewhere near the base.

22:30.717 --> 22:32.083
- What he said.

22:32.085 --> 22:33.851
- Mom, we stick together.
That's what we do.

22:33.853 --> 22:35.886
- We evaluate risk.
That's what we do.

22:35.888 --> 22:37.988
The smallest amount of risk
is me going up there alone.

22:37.990 --> 22:40.424
- You're not going alone.
I'm coming with you.

22:40.426 --> 22:41.625
- That's not necessary.

22:41.627 --> 22:43.928
- I have orders
to protect you.

22:43.930 --> 22:45.629
- I'll make sure these guys
don't get into trouble

22:45.631 --> 22:47.865
while you're gone.
- You better.

22:47.867 --> 22:49.967
I love you, okay?
- Just come back.

22:49.969 --> 22:52.503
- I will.

22:52.505 --> 22:55.573
- We should wait here
for you.

22:55.575 --> 22:57.475
- Mom, come with us
to the shelters.

22:57.477 --> 22:59.043
- This is not good-bye.

22:59.045 --> 23:02.380
- Please.
- I promise you.

23:02.382 --> 23:03.714
All right.
- Ready?

23:03.716 --> 23:05.149
- I'm ready.
- Good.

23:10.022 --> 23:11.455
See you tonight.

23:11.457 --> 23:18.396
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:33.579 --> 23:34.945
- I'm sorry.
I don't believe this.

23:34.947 --> 23:37.047
Who in the hell
walks up an exploding mountain?

23:37.049 --> 23:38.816
- Someone who's ready
to die for their family.

23:38.818 --> 23:40.117
- Nobody is dying.

23:40.119 --> 23:42.553
Nobody is dying.

23:42.555 --> 23:44.989
Got it?

23:44.991 --> 23:48.092
Where are we?

23:48.094 --> 23:50.995
- We're on track.

23:50.997 --> 23:52.430
I just saw a sign
for the shelter.

23:53.933 --> 23:56.901
[explosion]

24:05.545 --> 24:07.611
- Which way?

24:07.613 --> 24:10.548
[rumbling]

24:24.464 --> 24:27.131
- This way.
- Okay.

24:27.133 --> 24:29.733
- [whimpers]
- You okay?

24:29.735 --> 24:32.503
- No.
[grunts]

24:32.505 --> 24:35.072
- We have to keep moving.
- Just go on without me.

24:35.074 --> 24:37.908
- Danny bailed, too.
How'd that work out for him?

24:37.910 --> 24:39.610
- Danny didn't bail, Steve.

24:39.612 --> 24:42.079
He fell off your hold.

24:42.081 --> 24:44.715
We just left him there.
- Shut up, all right?

24:44.717 --> 24:46.817
He griped all the way up the
mountain, then he lost his edge.

24:46.819 --> 24:48.686
Hey, don't bogart the water!

24:48.688 --> 24:49.887
- Please.

24:49.889 --> 24:52.022
[vehicle approaching]

24:52.024 --> 24:56.093
- Hey! Oh!
- Hey! Hey!

24:57.663 --> 24:59.663
- Hey!
- Hey!

24:59.665 --> 25:02.766
- What do we got?
- Two people.

25:02.768 --> 25:04.735
- [groans]
Pull over.

25:04.737 --> 25:06.103
- Could be trouble.

25:06.105 --> 25:09.540
- I don't think so.
Let's stop.

25:09.542 --> 25:11.575
- Why chance it?
- Martin!

25:11.577 --> 25:14.778
- Hey!
- Anna, look out!

25:14.780 --> 25:16.080
- Martin, stop for them.

25:18.184 --> 25:20.050
- What are they doing?
Hey!

25:20.052 --> 25:22.219
[brakes squealing]

25:22.221 --> 25:23.821
Come on, come on.

25:23.823 --> 25:26.690
- Hey, he listened to me.
- Happy wife, happy life.

25:28.694 --> 25:30.961
- You, uh,
could've killed us.

25:30.963 --> 25:32.263
- Well, we didn't.

25:32.265 --> 25:34.899
- Nice way to start
a conversation, pal.

25:34.901 --> 25:36.934
- Whoa.
He's just stressed, okay?

25:36.936 --> 25:38.669
Look, our friend
fell into the crater,

25:38.671 --> 25:40.638
and we got caught in the steam,
and we, um--

25:40.640 --> 25:42.006
we just really need
a ride.

25:42.008 --> 25:44.074
- Your friend fell?
- Yeah, he froze up.

25:44.076 --> 25:45.543
- You let him go.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.011
- He was gonna fall anyways.
I chose to live.

25:47.013 --> 25:48.646
- We're headed
to the avalanche shelters.

25:48.648 --> 25:50.314
You can join us.

25:50.315 --> 25:51.981
- Uh, how you gonna do that?
There's too many of us.

25:51.984 --> 25:53.217
- So keep walking.

25:53.219 --> 25:54.818
- No, with this many people,

25:54.820 --> 25:56.287
there's only enough oxygen
in the shelters

25:56.289 --> 25:57.922
for a few hours,
at most.

25:57.924 --> 25:59.957
- Yeah, the only way out
is to keep driving.

25:59.959 --> 26:01.926
- Sorry. We can't do that.
- Our mother's on the volcano.

26:01.928 --> 26:04.194
- For real?
- She's dead.

26:04.196 --> 26:06.130
- Shut up about that!
You can join us or not.

26:06.132 --> 26:08.666
- The shelter
is a mistake.

26:08.668 --> 26:10.034
- Let's go. Come on, that's it.
- You got to keep driving.

26:10.036 --> 26:11.635
- Start walking, pal.

26:11.637 --> 26:13.137
- Uh...
[explosion]

26:13.139 --> 26:16.040
- Wait. Okay, okay,
yes, we'll take the ride, right?

26:16.042 --> 26:17.241
Thank you.

26:21.314 --> 26:23.347
- [exhales deeply]

26:23.349 --> 26:25.883
So you met a monk,
and he said there was a way

26:25.885 --> 26:27.318
to stop Rainier
from erupting?

26:27.320 --> 26:30.821
- Yeah, yeah.
- And you believe him?

26:30.823 --> 26:32.856
- Well, I got shot in the gut
with a rifle just today,

26:32.858 --> 26:34.825
and he cured it, so...

26:34.827 --> 26:36.193
- How?

26:36.195 --> 26:38.862
- I don't know that,
but it's gone.

26:38.864 --> 26:40.764
- So you believe the eruption
can be stopped,

26:40.766 --> 26:42.333
but you're heading
for a shelter

26:42.335 --> 26:45.269
because you think
the volcano might erupt?

26:45.271 --> 26:47.171
- Technically, yes, I guess--
I suppose that's true.

26:47.173 --> 26:48.973
- [chuckles]
That makes no sense.

26:48.975 --> 26:51.909
- Well, you two were trying
to climb up a volcano,

26:51.911 --> 26:54.111
and then your friend died.

26:56.382 --> 27:00.217
- But we're getting down alive,
no matter what.

27:13.299 --> 27:16.200
- [breathing heavily]

27:26.212 --> 27:28.912
What?

27:28.914 --> 27:31.281
- We've reached
our destination.

27:45.698 --> 27:48.432
[explosion]

28:00.046 --> 28:02.946
- This is it?
- Yes.

28:02.948 --> 28:06.083
- I thought
it was gonna be smaller...

28:06.085 --> 28:10.120
something
I could hold or...

28:10.122 --> 28:11.889
spin.

28:11.891 --> 28:14.992
- Evidently not.

28:14.994 --> 28:16.794
- Okay.

28:16.796 --> 28:19.096
So what do I do?

28:19.098 --> 28:21.165
- Step into the wheel,
and...

28:21.167 --> 28:22.966
oh, I assume
the rest will follow.

28:22.968 --> 28:25.402
- What if I'm not pure?

28:25.404 --> 28:27.771
- You're risking your life
to protect your family.

28:27.773 --> 28:30.040
What could be more pure
than this?

28:31.711 --> 28:33.777
- Step away, Karen.

28:33.779 --> 28:36.313
I'm walking
into that thing, not you.

28:42.188 --> 28:45.122
- Look, I don't like
these two, but...

28:45.124 --> 28:47.424
they could be right.

28:47.426 --> 28:49.860
- What?
You believe them?

28:49.862 --> 28:51.295
- Why would they lie?

28:51.297 --> 28:52.896
- 'Cause they're
random strangers

28:52.898 --> 28:54.331
we should not have
picked up.

28:54.333 --> 28:56.300
- Well, my dad is usually right
about things.

28:56.302 --> 28:58.736
- Your dad
is a fantastic guy,

28:58.738 --> 29:01.872
but the world is not set up
for fantastic guys anymore.

29:01.874 --> 29:05.476
You can't trust anyone.

29:05.478 --> 29:07.945
- You trust me.
- Because I love you.

29:07.947 --> 29:09.379
These two
are just arrogant clowns.

29:09.381 --> 29:11.381
They're gonna do whatever
they need, not what we need.

29:11.383 --> 29:14.051
- Okay, but can you just roll
the film back

29:14.053 --> 29:17.154
to--to when you said
that...

29:17.156 --> 29:18.989
- That I love you?

29:18.991 --> 29:20.390
- Yeah.

29:20.392 --> 29:23.393
- Sure.

29:23.395 --> 29:26.964
- But don't you think
it's kind of a big word?

29:29.401 --> 29:31.401
- I don't know.

29:31.403 --> 29:34.204
I mean...

29:34.206 --> 29:36.840
Devyn died
for your sister--

29:36.842 --> 29:39.343
literally died
rather than hurt her,

29:39.345 --> 29:44.047
and he knew her
for what, a week?

29:44.049 --> 29:48.051
The end of the world is making
everything mean more, Dana.

29:48.053 --> 29:50.154
You and me--we don't know
how much time we're gonna have,

29:50.156 --> 29:54.525
but my bet is we're gonna spend
all of it together.

29:56.796 --> 29:59.163
So we're, like...

29:59.165 --> 30:01.098
married, then?

30:01.100 --> 30:04.535
- [chuckles]
Well, we're something.

30:04.537 --> 30:07.171
Why don't we just
leave it at that?

30:07.173 --> 30:09.473
- Okay.

30:09.475 --> 30:11.842
But if we're, like...

30:11.844 --> 30:15.979
you know,
weirdly married...

30:15.981 --> 30:19.316
I would like to hold hands...

30:19.318 --> 30:20.450
or something.

30:20.452 --> 30:22.085
[chuckles]

30:22.087 --> 30:25.155
- Yeah,
that can be arranged.

30:25.157 --> 30:28.091
- [chuckles]

30:35.968 --> 30:37.434
- What are you doing?

30:37.436 --> 30:39.903
What are you doing?

30:39.905 --> 30:42.139
You're gonna shoot me
with my own gun?

30:42.141 --> 30:44.474
- I am walking
into the wheel, not you!

30:44.476 --> 30:46.276
- No, you're not.

30:46.278 --> 30:49.179
No, you're not,
and you're wasting time.

30:49.181 --> 30:51.114
- To do what--
take evil from the world?

30:51.116 --> 30:52.282
You can't stop this shit.

30:52.284 --> 30:53.584
All you can do is grab on

30:53.586 --> 30:55.152
to whatever happiness
you have left.

30:55.154 --> 30:57.020
And I want mine!
I want my son back!

30:57.022 --> 30:59.890
- Okay, okay.
- If you do this...

30:59.892 --> 31:02.192
you will not find
the results you seek.

31:02.194 --> 31:05.495
- A girl's got to dream.

31:05.497 --> 31:07.965
- [gasps]

31:07.967 --> 31:10.500
- You want to be next?

31:15.207 --> 31:16.540
- No.

31:18.611 --> 31:20.344
- Good.

31:20.346 --> 31:22.145
Here I go.

31:27.052 --> 31:30.020
- Okay, here's the shelter.

31:31.590 --> 31:34.391
[RV door closes]

31:34.393 --> 31:37.594
[Anna coughing]
Steve, hang on.

31:40.299 --> 31:42.532
- Hey, hey,
let me take that for you.

31:42.534 --> 31:44.601
All right, thanks. Yeah.
- Aah!

31:44.603 --> 31:46.203
- All right!
Everyone stay still!

31:46.205 --> 31:47.905
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!
- Let her go!

31:47.907 --> 31:49.339
- Put that thing down, now!

31:49.341 --> 31:51.074
- Steve.
- This is our thing now.

31:51.076 --> 31:52.342
Put the gun down.

31:52.344 --> 31:53.944
- [panting]

31:53.946 --> 31:56.146
- You go in there,
you're gonna die.

31:58.384 --> 32:00.217
- It's all the same to me.

32:00.219 --> 32:01.485
I'll see you around.

32:01.487 --> 32:03.253
[rumbling]

32:18.203 --> 32:20.270
- Don't! Don't!

32:20.272 --> 32:22.406
- [whimpers]
- Don't make me do this!

32:22.408 --> 32:24.508
- [voice breaking]
I just want my child back.

32:24.510 --> 32:26.043
[breathing heavily]

32:27.313 --> 32:29.346
Stop it!

32:29.348 --> 32:31.615
- [breathing heavily]

32:31.617 --> 32:33.517
- I'm getting my son.

32:42.728 --> 32:46.396
[breathing heavily]

32:48.233 --> 32:50.200
- Jane...
Jane--

32:50.202 --> 32:52.369
- He lied to us!

32:52.371 --> 32:53.670
Nothing's happening.

32:57.376 --> 33:00.043
Why can't I see my son?

33:03.082 --> 33:04.648
What the hell?

33:04.650 --> 33:06.249
What's happening?

33:06.251 --> 33:08.752
<i> [ominous music]</i>

33:08.754 --> 33:10.320
What the hell?

33:10.322 --> 33:12.322
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:12.324 --> 33:13.390
What the hell?

33:17.596 --> 33:21.098
- [breathing heavily]

33:24.036 --> 33:26.069
- I'll kill her.
- Oh, my God.

33:26.071 --> 33:27.504
- I'll kill her.

33:27.506 --> 33:29.339
- You're not strong enough
to kill my sister, you dickhead!

33:29.341 --> 33:31.675
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Guys, no guns. No guns, no guns!

33:31.677 --> 33:33.110
- Your dad's right.

33:33.112 --> 33:35.412
- Everyone put them down!
Relax!

33:35.414 --> 33:36.747
- Put your gun
on the ground now.

33:36.749 --> 33:38.248
- Here we go.

33:38.250 --> 33:39.716
What are you planning,
Steve?

33:39.718 --> 33:41.718
- Go get it.
Go get it!

33:41.720 --> 33:43.053
- Steve!
What's your plan?

33:45.224 --> 33:46.790
- Your plan is shit, man!

33:46.792 --> 33:48.658
You guys go hide
in those shelters if you want!

33:48.660 --> 33:50.027
We're taking your vehicle!

33:50.029 --> 33:51.161
- Your plan doesn't work.

33:51.163 --> 33:52.462
You have no time
to get down this mountain.

33:52.464 --> 33:54.164
- I'd rather die running
than hiding.

33:54.166 --> 33:55.365
- We'll all make it
in the shelters.

33:55.367 --> 33:56.433
We can still make it work.

33:56.435 --> 33:58.068
- Oh, did the monk
tell you that?

33:58.069 --> 33:59.702
- Everyone, relax!
- Just give us the keys, okay?

33:59.705 --> 34:01.271
- Go and take the keys,
you idiot.

34:01.273 --> 34:02.672
- Keys, all right.
- Keys, please.

34:02.674 --> 34:04.641
[panting]

34:04.643 --> 34:06.710
- Are you kidding me?

34:06.712 --> 34:08.678
Anna, get back here!
I'll go get them!

34:08.680 --> 34:10.313
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Hey.

34:10.315 --> 34:12.115
Just don't--
don't worry about that.

34:12.117 --> 34:14.718
Take a breath.
- [exhales deeply]

34:14.720 --> 34:16.319
- Okay, just put it down.
Put the gun down.

34:16.321 --> 34:17.454
- No.

34:17.456 --> 34:20.624
Don't tell me
what to do.

34:20.626 --> 34:23.326
- Hey, you're not killers.

34:23.328 --> 34:25.429
[scoffs]
You're climbers.

34:25.431 --> 34:27.097
- Martin, stop.

34:28.434 --> 34:29.499
- Just stop moving.

34:29.501 --> 34:31.635
- Just let her go.

34:31.637 --> 34:33.804
You're not gonna
shoot anyone.

34:33.806 --> 34:35.505
- Just stop moving.
- Just let her go.

34:35.507 --> 34:37.541
Let her go.
- Stop moving.

34:37.543 --> 34:39.576
- You're not gonna stab anyone
in the throat.

34:39.578 --> 34:42.746
[Anna crying]

34:42.748 --> 34:46.149
- So...

34:46.151 --> 34:47.651
So let's just.

35:02.468 --> 35:04.801
- Aah! Martin!

35:04.803 --> 35:06.803
No!
- What did you do?

35:06.805 --> 35:08.872
What the hell
did you just do?

35:08.874 --> 35:11.141
- Aah!

35:11.143 --> 35:13.877
- [crying]
No!

35:13.879 --> 35:17.380
[echoing]
No!

35:19.218 --> 35:21.785
[no audio]

35:24.356 --> 35:27.190
[girls screaming]

35:27.192 --> 35:29.192
- What the--

35:34.466 --> 35:37.367
- Sorry!
I'm so sorry!

35:37.369 --> 35:38.568
Steve...

35:38.570 --> 35:41.138
- Give me your belt.
- What?

35:41.140 --> 35:44.207
- Give me your belt!
- Okay, okay, okay.

35:44.209 --> 35:46.610
- [sobbing]
No!

35:46.612 --> 35:48.512
- Let's go!
- Okay, I'm trying.

35:48.514 --> 35:50.247
What are you doing?

35:50.249 --> 35:51.581
- Come here.

35:51.583 --> 35:52.749
- Please,
what are you doing?

35:52.751 --> 35:54.784
Please.
Please don't.

35:54.786 --> 35:58.455
What are you doing?
No! Steve...

35:58.457 --> 36:00.857
Please.
Please don't.

36:00.859 --> 36:02.425
Just don't, please.
I'm sorry.

36:02.427 --> 36:04.628
I'm sorr--
- Come with me.

36:04.630 --> 36:07.464
- What? Why?
- 'Cause I'm gonna hang you.

36:07.466 --> 36:09.399
- No! No! Aah!

36:09.401 --> 36:11.434
No! No!

36:11.436 --> 36:13.470
Aah! No!

36:13.472 --> 36:15.672
Aah!

36:15.674 --> 36:18.875
No! No!

36:18.877 --> 36:21.311
Steve! Steve!

36:21.313 --> 36:23.880
No! No!

36:23.882 --> 36:26.483
Aah! Aah!

36:28.187 --> 36:29.686
[grunting, panting]

36:35.661 --> 36:38.228
You don't have
to do this.

36:38.230 --> 36:39.829
You don't have
to do this!

36:39.831 --> 36:41.598
Please!

36:41.600 --> 36:44.668
Please!
[whimpering]

36:44.670 --> 36:47.771
Please.
[sobbing]

36:47.773 --> 36:50.907
- Matt.
- No, I'm not listening to you!

36:50.909 --> 36:53.243
I'm gonna get justice one
freakin' time in this world!

36:53.245 --> 36:55.512
- I'm so sorry.

36:55.514 --> 36:57.214
[grunts]
- Matt!

36:57.216 --> 36:59.583
Matt, if you kill her,
her blood is on you!

36:59.585 --> 37:01.451
- Please!

37:01.453 --> 37:03.620
Oh, please!

37:03.622 --> 37:04.688
- That's not right!

37:04.690 --> 37:06.389
Matt, that had nothing
to do with you!

37:06.391 --> 37:09.326
- Aah!
[choking]

37:12.598 --> 37:14.431
- Matt!

37:14.433 --> 37:17.300
- What do you want to do--
forgive them?

37:17.302 --> 37:18.401
- No, I want justice.

37:19.938 --> 37:22.772
- [choking]

37:22.774 --> 37:25.742
<i> [ominous music]</i>

37:25.744 --> 37:28.712
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:28.714 --> 37:31.448
- [gasps, coughing]

37:31.450 --> 37:34.284
[gasps, coughs]

37:34.286 --> 37:36.419
Get it--
get it off my neck!

37:36.421 --> 37:37.954
Get it off.

37:37.956 --> 37:40.323
- Hey! Hey!
On your knees.

37:40.325 --> 37:42.359
You touch that,
and I'll scalp you.

37:42.361 --> 37:44.995
- What are you gonna do,
tough guy, huh--kill us?

37:44.997 --> 37:46.963
- No, I'm not gonna kill you.
I'm not gonna wear your blood.

37:46.965 --> 37:48.465
The volcano's
gonna do it for me.

37:48.467 --> 37:49.899
But you're not getting
in the motor home,

37:49.901 --> 37:51.668
and you're not getting
in the shelter with us.

37:51.670 --> 37:53.770
You're gonna die under ten feet
of liquid burning rock.

37:53.772 --> 37:55.438
Get up. Get up!

37:55.440 --> 37:58.742
- She shot the guy!
I didn't do anything!

37:58.744 --> 38:01.544
- Put an ice pick
to my daughter's head!

38:01.546 --> 38:03.446
You gave a gun to a fool!

38:03.448 --> 38:05.615
And that fool
killed a good man,

38:05.617 --> 38:08.351
and that good man
loved my daughter.

38:08.353 --> 38:09.786
Now go! Go on!

38:13.892 --> 38:16.893
Is that fair?

38:16.895 --> 38:18.795
- Yeah, that's fair.

38:22.067 --> 38:24.734
[Dana sobbing]

38:24.736 --> 38:26.870
Martin!

38:26.872 --> 38:29.706
I don't want
to leave him here!

38:29.708 --> 38:31.708
- We won't, little girl.

38:31.710 --> 38:34.911
- You can't just leave us here!
- We're human beings!

38:34.913 --> 38:38.882
- Just miss them.
Leave them for the lava.

38:38.884 --> 38:40.817
[gunshots]

38:40.819 --> 38:42.886
- Go! Go, go!

38:42.888 --> 38:45.588
- Up, down, left, right--
it doesn't matter where you go!

38:45.590 --> 38:47.524
You're gonna die
in burning rock!

38:50.996 --> 38:54.030
[explosions, rumbling]

39:16.988 --> 39:18.621
- Mm-hmm.

39:18.623 --> 39:20.457
- You're alive?

39:24.096 --> 39:26.963
How? How? How?

39:26.965 --> 39:28.498
How are you alive?

39:28.500 --> 39:31.701
How are you alive?

39:31.703 --> 39:33.603
- Things happen.

39:39.578 --> 39:41.111
- I...I failed.

39:41.113 --> 39:44.948
- But your noble actions
merit reward.

39:44.950 --> 39:46.449
Look at me.

39:46.451 --> 39:48.485
Come with me.

39:52.557 --> 39:54.057
- Where?

39:54.059 --> 39:58.061
- To my next destination.

39:58.063 --> 40:00.463
Life can't be sustained here
any longer.

40:00.465 --> 40:01.898
You realize that.

40:03.969 --> 40:05.869
- Will my family be there?

40:07.639 --> 40:09.139
- I don't know.

40:09.141 --> 40:10.840
But every other delight
will be yours--

40:10.842 --> 40:15.612
security, rest, fulfillment.

40:15.614 --> 40:18.915
- I don't give up
on my family.

40:18.917 --> 40:20.884
- Even if they're going
to die?

40:20.886 --> 40:24.487
- You don't know that.

40:24.489 --> 40:26.189
And I'm gonna find out
for myself.

40:28.460 --> 40:30.160
- That's a beautiful choice.

40:33.632 --> 40:36.933
You really are coming along,
you know that?

40:36.935 --> 40:41.204
- You really are an asshole,
you know that?

40:41.206 --> 40:43.907
[groans]

40:45.677 --> 40:48.912
[explosion]

40:55.554 --> 40:57.520
[gasps]

41:02.060 --> 41:03.626
Oh.

41:04.763 --> 41:06.996
- [whimpering]
I need more time.

41:06.998 --> 41:08.565
- Dad, we have to go now!

41:08.567 --> 41:10.166
Dana, Dana...

41:10.168 --> 41:12.101
- Come on, Dana,
give me your hand.

41:12.103 --> 41:13.470
- I don't want
to leave him here.

41:13.472 --> 41:15.038
I don't want
to just leave him here.

41:15.040 --> 41:16.873
- Dana, Dana...
- Come on, Dana.

41:16.875 --> 41:19.843
[all shouting indistinctly]

41:19.845 --> 41:22.846
[Dana sobbing]

41:25.650 --> 41:28.585
[explosion]

41:37.896 --> 41:39.028
- Come on, come on, get in!

41:55.514 --> 41:57.580
[alarm blaring]

41:57.582 --> 41:59.782
Come on, come on, get in!
Get in!

41:59.784 --> 42:03.620
[Matt coughing]
- Where's Dana?

42:03.622 --> 42:05.655
Where's Dana?

42:05.657 --> 42:06.923
[shouting indistinctly]

42:06.925 --> 42:08.925
- Dad, you have to get in!
Dad, get in!

42:08.927 --> 42:10.093
- Dana!

42:17.769 --> 42:20.703
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

42:20.705 --> 42:27.644
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
